00141 /*
00142  *      In order to switch between files, we also
00143  *      need to save the buffer space too.
00144  */
00145 static int
00146 save_buffer (char line[], int len)
00147 {
00148   int i, ln;
00149   ln = yysptr - yysbuf;         /* number of characters in the buffer */
00150   for (i = 0; i < ln; i++)
00151     {
00152       if (i >= len)
00153         lex_punt ("failed to switch between files due to long buffer");
00154       line[i] = yysbuf[i];
00155     }
00156   yysptr = yysbuf;              /* empty buffer */
00157   return ln;
00158 }
00159 static void
00160 restore_buffer (char line[], int len)
00161 {
00162   int i;
00163   yysptr = yysbuf;              /* empty buffer */
00164   for (i = 0; i < len; i++)
00165     {
00166       *yysptr = line[i];
00167       yysptr++;
00168     }
00169 }

00685 static void
00686 push_file (void)
00687 {
00688   stack[stack_top] = yyin;
00689   fname[stack_top] = currentFile;
00690   fline[stack_top] = currentLine;
00691   fcolumn[stack_top] = currentColumn;
00692   buf_length[stack_top] =
00693     save_buffer (buf_data[stack_top], MAX_BUF_DATA_SIZE);
00694   currentFile = "???";
00695   currentLine = 1;
00696   currentColumn = 1;
00697   stack_top += 1;
00698   if (stack_top >= MAX_LEVEL)
00699     lex_punt ("too many levels of file inclusion");

00701 static void
00702 pop_file (void)
00703 {
00704   if (stack_top <= 0)
00705     {
00706       lex_punt ("pop_file: stack underflows");
00707     }
00708   stack_top -= 1;
00709   yyin = stack[stack_top];
00710   currentLine = fline[stack_top];
00711   currentColumn = fcolumn[stack_top];
00712   currentFile = fname[stack_top];
00713   restore_buffer (buf_data[stack_top], buf_length[stack_top]);
00714 }

00736 /* 
00737  *      Set Up The Input File.
00738  */
00739 int
00740 Cl_open (char *file_name, int inclusion)
00741 {
00742   FILE *fpt;
00743   char *last_file;
00744   INIT ();
00745   push_file ();         
00746   last_file = currentFile;
00747 
00748   /* Moved yyin and yyout initialization here. -JCG 5/99 */
00749   yyin = stdin;
00750   yyout = stdout;
00751 
00752   /*
00753    *  If the current_file is specified from the
00754    *  root directory, do nothing.
00755    *  Otherwise, add the prefix of the last file
00756    *  to the front of the file_name.
00757    */
00758   if (inclusion && (last_file != 0) && (file_name[0] != '/'))
00759     {
00760       int len, j, i;
00761       char temp1[1024];
00762       len = strlen (last_file);
00763       /* find the prefix: /x/y/z -> /x/y */
00764       for (i = len - 1; i >= 0; i--)
00765         if (last_file[i] == '/')
00766           break;
00767       for (j = 0; j <= i; j++)
00768         temp1[j] = last_file[j];
00769       for (i = 0; i <= strlen (file_name); i++)
00770         temp1[i + j] = file_name[i];
00771       file_name = SAVE (temp1);
00772     }
00773   currentFile = SAVE (file_name);  
00774   if (!strcmp (file_name, "stdin"))
00775     {
00776       yyin = stdin;
00777       return 1;
00778     }
00779   else
00780     {                           /* open new file */
00781       fpt = fopen (file_name, "r");
00782       if (fpt == NULL)
00783         {
00784           /*
00785            *  Since we have already save the state
00786            *  of the last file, we cannot simply
00787            *  return to the caller. If future
00788            *  versions requires this to return,
00789            *  need to close up the file first.
00790            */
00791           fprintf (stderr, "> %s\n", file_name);
00792           lex_punt ("can not open file");
00793           Cl_close (file_name);
00794           return 0;
00795         }
00796       yyin = fpt;
00797       return 1;
00798     }
00799 }

00833 static Cl_List
00834 new_node (void)
00835 {
00836   Cl_List new_list;
00837   if (dead_list != 0)
00838     {
00839       new_list = dead_list;
00840       dead_list = Cl_SiblingOf (dead_list);
00841     }
00842   else
00843     {
00844       new_list = (Cl_List) C_malloc (sizeof (_Cl_List));
00845     }
00846   Cl_NodeType (new_list) = Cl_NULL;
00847   Cl_StringOf (new_list) = "???";
00848   Cl_SiblingOf (new_list) = 0;
00849   return new_list;
00850 }
00851 /*
00852  *      Dispose space of a node and its siblings and descendants.       
00853  */
00854 Cl_List Cl_dispose (Cl_List node)
00855 {
00856   if (node == 0)
00857     return 0;
00858   if ((Cl_NodeType (node) == Cl_LIST) || (Cl_NodeType (node) == Cl_STD_GROUP)
00859       || (Cl_NodeType (node) == Cl_OPT_GROUP)
00860       || (Cl_NodeType (node) == Cl_OPT_SYNC))
00861     {
00862       Cl_dispose (Cl_ChildOf (node));
00863       Cl_ChildOf (node) = 0;
00864     }
00865   Cl_dispose (Cl_SiblingOf (node));
00866   Cl_SiblingOf (node) = dead_list;      /* add node to the dead list */
00867   dead_list = node;             /* for recycling */
00868   return 0;
00869 }
00870 /*      
00871  *      Add a child.    
00872  */
00873 static void
00874 add_child (Cl_List parent, Cl_List child)
00875 {
00876   Cl_List ptr;
00877   if (Cl_ChildOf (parent) == 0)
00878     {
00879       /* the first child */
00880       Cl_ChildOf (parent) = child;
00881     }
00882   else
00883     {
00884       /* find last child */
00885       for (ptr = Cl_ChildOf (parent); Cl_SiblingOf (ptr) != 0;)
00886         ptr = Cl_SiblingOf (ptr);
00887       /* append the new child to it */
00888       Cl_SiblingOf (ptr) = child;
00889     }
00890 }

00892 /*
00893  *      Get a node or a complete list from input.
00894  *      It is assumed that the lexer has been properly set up.
00895  */
00896 Cl_List Cl_get (void)
00897 {
00898   int node_type;
00899   Cl_List new_list, ptr;
00900   node_type = yylex ();         /* get token */
00901   if (node_type == 0)
00902     {                           /* end of file */
00903       new_list = new_node ();
00904       Cl_NodeType (new_list) = Cl_EOF;
00905       Cl_StringOf (new_list) = "<EOF>";
00906       Cl_File (new_list) = TokenFile;
00907       Cl_Line (new_list) = TokenLine;
00908       Cl_Column (new_list) = TokenColumn;
00909       return new_list;
00910     }
00911   switch (node_type)
00912     {
00913     case L_ID:                  /* identifier */
00914       new_list = new_node ();
00915       Cl_NodeType (new_list) = Cl_ID;
00916       Cl_StringOf (new_list) = SAVE (TokenName);
00917       Cl_File (new_list) = TokenFile;
00918       Cl_Line (new_list) = TokenLine;
00919       Cl_Column (new_list) = TokenColumn;
00920       break;
00921     case L_INT:         /* integer */
00922       new_list = new_node ();
00923       Cl_NodeType (new_list) = Cl_INT;
00924       Cl_StringOf (new_list) = SAVE2 (TokenName);
00925       Cl_IntegerOf (new_list) = TokenInteger;
00926       Cl_File (new_list) = TokenFile;
00927       Cl_Line (new_list) = TokenLine;
00928       Cl_Column (new_list) = TokenColumn;
00929       break;
00930     case L_REAL:                /* real constant literal */
00931       new_list = new_node ();
00932       Cl_NodeType (new_list) = Cl_REAL;
00933       Cl_StringOf (new_list) = SAVE2 (TokenName);
00934       Cl_RealOf (new_list) = TokenReal;
00935       Cl_File (new_list) = TokenFile;
00936       Cl_Line (new_list) = TokenLine;
00937       Cl_Column (new_list) = TokenColumn;
00938       break;
00939     case L_STRING:              /* string literal */
00940       new_list = new_node ();
00941       Cl_NodeType (new_list) = Cl_STRING;
00942       Cl_StringOf (new_list) = SAVE (TokenName);
00943       Cl_File (new_list) = TokenFile;
00944       Cl_Line (new_list) = TokenLine;
00945       Cl_Column (new_list) = TokenColumn;
00946       break;
00947     case L_CHAR:                /* character literal */
00948       new_list = new_node ();
00949       Cl_NodeType (new_list) = Cl_CHAR;
00950       Cl_StringOf (new_list) = SAVE (TokenName);
00951       Cl_File (new_list) = TokenFile;
00952       Cl_Line (new_list) = TokenLine;
00953       Cl_Column (new_list) = TokenColumn;
00954       break;
00955     case L_ERROR:               /* erroneous input */
00956       new_list = new_node ();
00957       Cl_NodeType (new_list) = Cl_NULL;
00958       Cl_StringOf (new_list) = SAVE (TokenName);
00959       Cl_File (new_list) = TokenFile;
00960       Cl_Line (new_list) = TokenLine;
00961       Cl_Column (new_list) = TokenColumn;
00962       break;
00963     case L_MACRO:
00964       /* remove everything until \n */
00965       while ((ptr = Cl_get ()) != 0)
00966         {
00967           if (Cl_NodeType (ptr) == Cl_EOF)
00968             {
00969               Cl_dispose (ptr);
00970               break;
00971             }

00973         }
00974       new_list = Cl_get ();
00975       break;
00976     case L_EOLN:
00977       new_list = 0;
00978       break;
00979     case '(':
00980       new_list = new_node ();
00981       Cl_NodeType (new_list) = Cl_LIST;
00982       Cl_StringOf (new_list) = "()";
00983       Cl_ChildOf (new_list) = 0;
00984       Cl_File (new_list) = TokenFile;
00985       Cl_Line (new_list) = TokenLine;
00986       Cl_Column (new_list) = TokenColumn;
00987       while ((ptr = Cl_get ()) != 0)
00988         {
00989           if (Cl_NodeType (ptr) == Cl_EOF)
00990             lex_punt ("detect EOF when expecting )");
00991           add_child (new_list, ptr);
00992         }
00993       break;
00994     case '[':
00995       new_list = new_node ();
00996       Cl_NodeType (new_list) = Cl_STD_GROUP;
00997       Cl_StringOf (new_list) = "[]";
00998       Cl_ChildOf (new_list) = 0;
00999       Cl_File (new_list) = TokenFile;
01000       Cl_Line (new_list) = TokenLine;
01001       Cl_Column (new_list) = TokenColumn;
01002       while ((ptr = Cl_get ()) != 0)
01003         {
01004           if (Cl_NodeType (ptr) == Cl_EOF)
01005             lex_punt ("detect EOF when expecting ]");
01006           add_child (new_list, ptr);
01007         }
01008       break;
01009     case '<':
01010       new_list = new_node ();
01011       Cl_NodeType (new_list) = Cl_OPT_GROUP;
01012       Cl_StringOf (new_list) = "<>";
01013       Cl_ChildOf (new_list) = 0;
01014       Cl_File (new_list) = TokenFile;
01015       Cl_Line (new_list) = TokenLine;
01016       Cl_Column (new_list) = TokenColumn;
01017       while ((ptr = Cl_get ()) != 0)
01018         {
01019           if (Cl_NodeType (ptr) == Cl_EOF)
01020             lex_punt ("detect EOF when expecting >");
01021           add_child (new_list, ptr);
01022         }
01023       break;
01024     case '{':
01025       new_list = new_node ();
01026       Cl_NodeType (new_list) = Cl_OPT_SYNC;
01027       Cl_StringOf (new_list) = "{}";
01028       Cl_ChildOf (new_list) = 0;
01029       Cl_File (new_list) = TokenFile;
01030       Cl_Line (new_list) = TokenLine;
01031       Cl_Column (new_list) = TokenColumn;
01032       while ((ptr = Cl_get ()) != 0)
01033         {
01034           if (Cl_NodeType (ptr) == Cl_EOF)
01035             lex_punt ("detect EOF when expecting }");
01036           add_child (new_list, ptr);
01037         }
01038       break;
01039     case ')':
01040     case ']':
01041     case '>':
01042     case '}':
01043       new_list = 0;
01044       break;
01045     default:                    /* single character operator */
01046       new_list = new_node ();
01047       Cl_NodeType (new_list) = Cl_OPER;
01048       Cl_StringOf (new_list) = SAVE (TokenName);
01049       Cl_IntegerOf (new_list) = node_type;
01050       Cl_File (new_list) = TokenFile;
01051       Cl_Line (new_list) = TokenLine;
01052       Cl_Column (new_list) = TokenColumn;
01053       break;
01054     }
01055   return new_list;
01056 }

01157 /*      print a node.
01158  *      this is useful for program debugging.
01159  */
01160 static FILE *FF = NULL;
01161 static void
01162 print_node (Cl_List node, int indent)
01163 {
01164   int i;
01165   Cl_List ptr;
01166   if (FF == NULL)
01167     FF = stdout;
01168   if (node == 0)
01169     return;
01170   for (i = 0; i < indent; i++)
01171     fprintf (FF, " ");
01172   switch (Cl_NodeType (node))
01173     {
01174     case Cl_EOF:
01175       break;
01176     case Cl_NULL:
01177       fprintf (FF, "???");
01178       break;
01179     case Cl_LIST:
01180       fprintf (FF, "(\n");
01181       for (ptr = Cl_ChildOf (node); ptr != 0; ptr = Cl_SiblingOf (ptr))
01182         {
01183           print_node (ptr, indent + 2);
01184           fprintf (FF, "\n");
01185         }
01186       for (i = 0; i < indent; i++)
01187         fprintf (FF, " ");
01188       fprintf (FF, ")");
01189       break;
01190     case Cl_ID:
01191       fprintf (FF, "%s", Cl_StringOf (node));
01192       break;
01193     case Cl_INT:
01194       fprintf (FF, ITintmaxformat, Cl_IntegerOf (node));
01195       break;
01196     case Cl_REAL:
01197       fprintf (FF, "%f", Cl_RealOf (node));
01198       break;
01199     case Cl_STRING:
01200       fprintf (FF, "%s", Cl_StringOf (node));
01201       break;
01202     case Cl_CHAR:
01203       fprintf (FF, "%s", Cl_StringOf (node));
01204       break;
01205     case Cl_OPER:
01206       fprintf (FF, "%c", (char) Cl_IntegerOf (node));
01207       break;
01208     case Cl_MACRO:
01209     case Cl_EOLN:
01210       fprintf (FF, "%s", Cl_StringOf (node));
01211       break;
01212     case Cl_STD_GROUP:
01213       fprintf (FF, "[\n");
01214       for (ptr = Cl_ChildOf (node); ptr != 0; ptr = Cl_SiblingOf (ptr))
01215         {
01216           print_node (ptr, indent + 2);
01217           fprintf (FF, "\n");
01218         }
01219       for (i = 0; i < indent; i++)
01220         fprintf (FF, " ");
01221       fprintf (FF, "]");
01222       break;
01223     case Cl_OPT_GROUP:
01224       fprintf (FF, "<\n");
01225       for (ptr = Cl_ChildOf (node); ptr != 0; ptr = Cl_SiblingOf (ptr))
01226         {
01227           print_node (ptr, indent + 2);
01228           fprintf (FF, "\n");
01229         }
01230       for (i = 0; i < indent; i++)
01231         fprintf (FF, " ");
01232       fprintf (FF, ">");
01233       break;
01234     case Cl_OPT_SYNC:
01235       fprintf (FF, "{\n");
01236       for (ptr = Cl_ChildOf (node); ptr != 0; ptr = Cl_SiblingOf (ptr))
01237         {
01238           print_node (ptr, indent + 2);
01239           fprintf (FF, "\n");
01240         }
01241       for (i = 0; i < indent; i++)
01242         fprintf (FF, " ");
01243       fprintf (FF, "}");
01244       break;
01245     default:
01246       fprintf (FF, "???");
01247       break;
01248     }
01249 }

01265  */
01266 Cl_List Cl_integer (Cl_List list, C_Integer * val)
01267 {
01268   Cl_List ptr;
01269   int sign;
01270   ptr = list;
01271   if (ptr == 0)
01272     {
01273       *val = 0;
01274       return 0;
01275     }
01276   sign = 1;
01277   while (Cl_NodeType (ptr) == Cl_OPER)
01278     {
01279       if ((char) Cl_IntegerOf (ptr) == '-')
01280         {
01281           sign = -sign;
01282         }
01283       else if ((char) Cl_IntegerOf (ptr) == '+')
01284         {
01285         }
01286       else
01287         {
01288           *val = 0;
01289           return list;
01290         }
01291       ptr = Cl_SiblingOf (ptr);
01292       if (ptr == 0)
01293         break;
01294     }
01295   if (ptr == 0)
01296     {
01297       *val = 0;
01298       return list;
01299     }
01300   if (Cl_NodeType (ptr) != Cl_INT)
01301     {
01302       *val = 0;
01303       return list;
01304     }
01305   *val = (Cl_IntegerOf (ptr) * sign);
01306   return Cl_SiblingOf (ptr);
01307 }
